HEADWORD: diestrus
<hw>diestrus</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a state or interval of sexual
inactivity or quiescence between periods of activity; -- of animals
having several estrous cycles in one breeding season.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> diestrum.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

